Ecological notes : very common in broad-leaved and carr woodland; heathland; water meadows and gravel pits; old hedges; within Ouse Washes bird hide; wooded river bank; calcareous grassland; parkland; gardens. Reared from rotten wood. iii–vii, ix, xi.
